          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " T(p,n)He-3 for the neutron energy range",
                " 0.9 - 4. MeV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " D(d,n)T reaction for the energy range",
                " 4.7 - 8.3 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detection of gamma-rays The sample was",
                "placed  on the axis and inclined at an angle of 45 deg.",
                "with respect to the incident beam.",
                " Time-of-flight techniques were used to improve the",
                " signal to background ratio."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  NaI crystal, 20.8 cm long, 22.6 cm diameter,",
                " shielded and viewed by seven photomultipliers RCA 8054"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " long counter placed at 135 deg. to the ion-beam",
                " as monitor"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "4PI1A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  4pi*90 degree cross section value.",
                " The area under the normalized response",
                " function was used to determine the cross section for",
                " neutron capture leading to the emission of a gamma-ray",
                " of the corresponding energy.",
                " The cross section was determined by a straight-forward",
                " calculation using the integrated target beam current",
                " and the gas pressure to obtain the neutron flux"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The given cross sections have been evaluated for high-",
                " energy gamma-ray transitions from capturing state to",
                " low-lying states in the residual nuclei.",
                " A comparison between these cross sections and calcul-",
                " ations based on semi-direct capture theories shows",
                " that the semi-direct capture processes are important",
                " to explain the magnitude and energy variation of the",
                " neutron capture cross section in the region of the",
                " electric dipole giant resonance."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " At each neutron energy several runs were performed",
                " with sample in and sample out to reduce the influence",
                " of small fluctuations in background and drift in the",
                " electronic circuits.",
                " Corrections due to neutron and gamma-ray attenuation",
                " in the sample, to the attenuation of gamma-rays in",
                " lithium hydride and lead placed in front of the",
                " detector and to neutron multiple scattering in the",
                " sample were calculated and taken into account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The estimated total error",
                " The dominating error in the cross section",
                " originates from the unfolding calculation of the",
                " gamma-ray spectra."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": 15.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The maximum total error resulting from the",
                " unfolding procedure was estimated never to exceed",
                " 15% for the highest gamma-ray peak."
              ]
            }
          ],
